ZTE has launched its Quartz Smart Watch, which features Android Wear 2.0 and cellular connectivity. The watch will be released on 14 April and will sell for $192 in the US. The device features: The Quartz watch also supports Google Assistant and the new features of Android Wear 2.0. ZTE said users can use the watch in tandem with their smartphone or as a standalone device with Wi-Fi and cellular data support. It further features customisable watch faces and interchangeable wrist bands.